TASK_DESCRIPTION=Research Charmbracelet's approach to AI CLI UX (Mods, Crush, Glow, Bubble Tea patterns) and apply relevant best practices to the doey intent fallback (shell/intent-fallback.sh + shell/doey-intent-dispatch.sh). Focus areas likely include: streaming output with spinners, clear affirmation/confirmation prompts for destructive actions, colorized diff/suggestion display, consistent prompt framing, graceful cancellation, minimal cognitive load. Phase 1: research (fetch Charmbracelet docs/repos — Mods https://github.com/charmbracelet/mods is the closest analog). Phase 2: produce a concrete list of proposed UX changes for user approval. Phase 3: implement after approval. Related in-flight task: #450 (fallback speed). Consider coordinating.
